{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.21",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 21 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:1",
      "text": "My son, have you sinned? Do it no more; and ask forgiveness for your past sins.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:2",
      "text": "Flee from sin as from the face of a snake; for if you go near, it will bite you. Its teeth are like lion’s teeth, slaying people’s souls.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:3",
      "text": "All iniquity is as a two-edged sword. Its stroke has no healing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:4",
      "text": "Terror and violence will waste away riches. So the house of an arrogant man will be laid waste.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:5",
      "text": "Supplication from a poor man’s mouth reaches to the ears of God, and his judgment comes speedily.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:6",
      "text": "One who hates reproof is in the path of the sinner. He who fears the Lord will repent in his heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:7",
      "text": "He who is mighty in tongue is known far away; but the man of understanding knows when he slips.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:8",
      "text": "He who builds his house with other men’s money is like one who gathers stones for his own tomb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:9",
      "text": "The congregation of wicked men is as a bundle of tow with a flame of fire at the end of them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:10",
      "text": "The way of sinners is paved with stones; and at the end of it is the pit of Hades.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:11",
      "text": "He who keeps the law becomes master of its intent. The fulfilment of the fear of the Lord is wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:12",
      "text": "He who is not clever will not be instructed. There is a cleverness which makes bitterness abound.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:13",
      "text": "The knowledge of a wise man will be made to abound as a flood, and his counsel as a fountain of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:14",
      "text": "The inward parts of a fool are like a broken vessel. He will hold no knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:15",
      "text": "If a man of knowledge hears a wise word, he will commend it and add to it. The wanton man hears it, and it displeases him, so he throws it away behind his back.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:16",
      "text": "The chatter of a fool is like a burden in the way, but grace will be found on the lips of the wise.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:17",
      "text": "The utterance of the prudent man will be sought for in the congregation. They will ponder his words in their heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:18",
      "text": "As a house that is destroyed, so is wisdom to a fool. The knowledge of an unwise man is talk without sense.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:19",
      "text": "Instruction is as fetters on the feet of an unwise man, and as manacles on the right hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:20",
      "text": "A fool lifts up his voice with laughter, but a clever man smiles quietly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:21",
      "text": "Instruction is to a prudent man as an ornament of gold, and as a bracelet upon his right arm.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:22",
      "text": "The foot of a fool rushes into a house, but a man of experience will be ashamed of entering.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:23",
      "text": "A foolish man peers into the door of a house, but a man who is instructed will stand outside.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:24",
      "text": "It is rude for someone to listen at a door, but a prudent person will be grieved with the disgrace.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:25",
      "text": "The lips of strangers will be grieved at these things, but the words of prudent men will be weighed in the balance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:26",
      "text": "The heart of fools is in their mouth, but the mouth of wise men is their heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:27",
      "text": "When the ungodly curses an adversary, he curses his own soul.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.21.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 21:28",
      "text": "A whisperer defiles his own soul, and will be hated wherever he travels.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
